." Manpage for laptop-doctor
.TH LAPTOP-DOCTOR 1 "July 2026" "1.0" "Laptop Doctor Subcommand Manual"
.SH NAME
laptop-doctor \- Show laptop version, update status and environment health
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B laptop doctor
.SH DESCRIPTION
The doctor subcommand reports the health of your laptop installation.
It runs a series of checks and displays their results in a human-readable format.
.PP
Shipped checks (in order):
.RS
.TP
.B version
Current installed version, latest available version, and update status (\fIup-to-date\fR or \fIoutdated\fR).
.TP
.B install
Installation method (brew, git, or manual) and the LAPTOP_HOME path.
.TP
.B profile
Active profile name and whether it resolves to a known profile.
.TP
.B disk
Available disk space on the root filesystem.
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
None. Use parent command options:
.TP
.B --color \fImode\fR
Enable or disable ANSI colors (auto, always, never).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B laptop doctor
Run all doctor checks and display results.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR laptop (1),
.BR laptop-self-upgrade (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Written by jpolo.
